a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-1))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 6) (Im 2)"
shows  "a * b = 20"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $(3-i)(6+2i)$. The final Answer is 20
 ### Proof
 $(3-i)(6+2i) = 3(6) + 3(2i) -i(6) -i(2i) = 18+6i-6i +2 = \boxed{20}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-1))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 6) (Im 2)"
shows  "a * b = 20"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the product of the complex numbers $(3 - i)$ and $(6 + 2i)$. The final answer is $20$.
